Task 1 I designed a digital literacy infographic on Canva. The goal of the infographic was to highlight the fundamental concepts of digital literacy in a fun, clean, and clear manner, which is helpful for students to learn and implement in their day-to-day life. My infographic has four sections, which are; digital literacy definition, using internet safely, helpful digital tools for students and email etiquette. These sections each point out important issues, such as protecting personal information on the internet and the usage of stronger passwords to prevent intrusion. It also touches upon making appropriate digital communication through emailing, for instance in professional environment. The design process of the infographic included the importance of not overloading the infographic with text and at the same time ensuring all information was delivered clearly. I found it fun and interesting using Canva to combine elements such as icons and using different types of font combination for headings and contents. The one problem that I found was fitting the information onto the one page, without appearing too congested, though I did learn a lot about digital design, its capabilities and importance of having a clean design.
